column5: That kid of ours woke up this morning but, unfortunatly one of her zoo members (Rosie) didn't...  She will always be with you in your heart...
Sad news Norm, Maureen sure does love her dogs.
Ya, saw that on Facebook, so sorry Mo, they are our babies
To go while sleeping is about as good as you can ask for right.  That's a fine looking dog.  I bet you guys had lots of good times!
Sorry to hear, part of the family for sure
Sorry for your loss, its always hard to lose a friend
So sad Maureen to go in their sleep is for the best.   Art
Sorry to hear. Looks like she made the call and you didn't have to.
So sorry to hear?  So many of us have been through it and it always sucks  Cherish the many many great memories
She couldn't have had a better life than to be with you! I am so sorry for your loss
Sorry for your loss, a true friend for sure.
Sorry for your loss Maureen.  Take Care
So sorry for your loss cherish the memories.
So sorry to hear his news Mo.  My thoughts are with you.
My condolences to all of you.

Thanks everyone, it was a bit of a shock as she hadn,t been sick at all, everything was normal when I went to bed.  I picked Rosie up a little over three years ago from the Brampton animal shelter. I can't get over how quiet the house is without her....she was always barking... lol ... never thought I would miss that.  Thanks again Maureen
